# Data Updates: Migrations vs Re-scraping

Two approaches to update data. Choose based on the source of truth.

## Migrations (DB-only)

Use when transforming existing data without needing fresh external data.

**Examples**: field renames, data format changes, backfilling computed fields.

**Location**: `convex/migrations/`

## Re-scraping (via Queue)

Use when you need fresh data from Amazon. **Never create new scraping scripts** — use the existing queue system.

### Queue a re-scrape

```typescript
// Full re-scrape (discovers authors, series, etc.)
await client.mutation(api.scrapeQueue.mutations.enqueue, {
  url: 'https://amazon.com/dp/...',
  type: 'book', // or 'series' | 'author'
})

// Focused re-scrape (skip side-effects)
await client.mutation(api.scrapeQueue.mutations.queueRescrape, {
  entityType: 'book',
  entityId: bookId,
  skipAuthorDiscovery: true, // Don't queue author pages
  skipSeriesLink: true, // Don't link/create series
  skipCoverDownload: true, // Don't re-download cover
})
```

### Key files

| File                              | Purpose                                         |
| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `convex/scrapeQueue/mutations.ts` | `enqueue`, `queueRescrape` — add items to queue |
| `scripts/worker/index.ts`         | Worker that processes queued items              |
| `scripts/worker/processors/`      | Processing logic per entity type                |

### Skip flags for `queueRescrape`

- `skipSeriesLink` — Don't link book to series
- `skipAuthorDiscovery` — Don't queue author pages
- `skipBookDiscoveries` — Don't queue books from series/author
- `skipCoverDownload` — Don't download cover image

## Decision guide

| Need                                 | Approach  |
| ------------------------------------ | --------- |
| Transform existing field values      | Migration |
| Fix scraper bug, need fresh data     | Re-scrape |
| Add new field from external source   | Re-scrape |
| Rename field, change format          | Migration |
| Update cover/URL/details from Amazon | Re-scrape |
